# Premises:
University(yale)
Private(yale)
IvyLeague(yale)
Research(yale)

LocatedIn(yale, newHaven)
# The year Yale moved to New Haven is explicitly stated.
# A more precise predicate could be MoveYear(yale, newHaven, 1716), but Year(1716) is kept for consistency with the original.
Year(1716)
EndowmentValue(yale, 42.3, billion)
OrganizedInto(yale, 27) # Yale is organized into 27 constituent colleges and schools.

# Explicitly listing the 14 residential colleges and asserting they are residential colleges and constituents of Yale.

ConstituentType(trumbullCollege, ResidentialCollege)

# Asserting the existence and naming of the Yale Graduate School of Arts and Sciences.
Constituent(yaleGraduateSchool, yale)
CollegeOrSchoolName(yaleGraduateSchool, "Yale Graduate School of Arts and Sciences")
ConstituentType(yaleGraduateSchool, GraduateSchool)

# Asserting the existence of 12 professional schools.
# We use a single predicate to assert the existence of 12 distinct professional schools.
# The logic here implies that there are exactly 12 professional schools, and they are all constituents of Yale.
# The distinctness of these 12 schools is implicitly handled by existential quantification over distinct variables in standard FOL.

    Constituent(ps1, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps1, ProfessionalSchool)
    ∧ Constituent(ps2, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps2, ProfessionalSchool)
    ∧ Constituent(ps3, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps3, ProfessionalSchool)
    ∧ Constituent(ps4, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps4, ProfessionalSchool)
    ∧ Constituent(ps5, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps5, ProfessionalSchool)
    ∧ Constituent(ps6, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps6, ProfessionalSchool)
    ∧ Constituent(ps7, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps7, ProfessionalSchool)
    ∧ Constituent(ps8, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps8, ProfessionalSchool)
    ∧ Constituent(ps9, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps9, ProfessionalSchool)
    ∧ Constituent(ps10, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps10, ProfessionalSchool)
    ∧ Constituent(ps11, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps11, ProfessionalSchool)
    ∧ Constituent(ps12, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps12, ProfessionalSchool)
    # Explicitly stating that there are exactly 12 professional schools.
    # This is done by asserting that any entity that is a professional school and a constituent of yale must be one of these 12.
    # This also enforces distinctness among ps1 to ps12 implicitly in standard FOL interpretation.
    # For full explicit distinctness, one would need to add:
    # ps1 != ps2, ps1 != ps3, ..., ps11 != ps12
    # However, this is often assumed by the existential quantifier for distinct variables.
    ∧ ForAll ps_any. (
        (Constituent(ps_any, yale) ∧ ConstituentType(ps_any, ProfessionalSchool))
        =>
        (ps_any = ps1 ∨ ps_any = ps2 ∨ ps_any = ps3 ∨ ps_any = ps4 ∨ ps_any = ps5 ∨ ps_any = ps6 ∨ ps_any = ps7 ∨ ps_any = ps8 ∨ ps_any = ps9 ∨ ps_any = ps10 ∨ ps_any = ps11 ∨ ps_any = ps12)
    )
)

¬∃x (University(x) ∧ EndowmentValue(x, y) ∧ y > 42300000000)
